        <div xml:id="OTP33218500">
        <fw type="pageNum">Letter from W. A. Wilson to Mississippi Governor Benjamin G. Humphreys; Undated</fw>
          <p corresp='TTP33218500P0' xml:id='OTP33218500P0'>[seal]
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33218500P1' xml:id='OTP33218500P1'>Messrs. <rs ref='#S32121928'>Poval</rs>. &amp; <rs ref='#S32121897'>Allen</rs>.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33218500P2' xml:id='OTP33218500P2'>Gents.
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33218500P3' xml:id='OTP33218500P3'>If this Case of Allen Burns is the one wherein he was <rs ref='#S25025235'>charged</rs> with <rs ref='#S25012377'>appropriating Commanders horse</rs> I will mention to you that he was <rs ref='#S32019844'>released</rs> by the <rs ref='#S32085304'>Civil</rs> and turned over to the Military Authority where he was punished for it and any other <rs ref='#S32074731'>Charges</rs> preferred against him. Is it right to renew those Charges? and try and Condemn him again after he was once tried Condemned and released and punished by the Military This is Strictly So, make of it what you See fit
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33218500P4' xml:id='OTP33218500P4'>Yours [gap] <rs ref='#S25014512'>W. A. Wilson</rs>
</p>


        </div>
  </body>
